The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) has said only those who have Permanent Voters Cards (PVCs) would be eligible to vote in the July 16 governorship election in Osun State. Speaking at a stakeholders’ meeting on the governorship election, the INEC Resident Electoral Commissioner in the state, Professor Abdulganiy Olayinka, urged residents to ensure that they got their PVCs to be able to vote for candidates of their choice. Supreme Court okays new online fee payment method Corruption fueling political instability in W/Africa – ICPC He insisted on “No PVC, No Voting” and urged those who have not collected theirs to do so without further delay.